             and -- Holman deposed, they saw a Man come out of the Reed-Loft with his Coat off, but could not swear the Prisoner was the Person. 
               <persName id="t17200712-23-person161">
                  Susannah 
                  Harlow 
               <interp inst="t17200712-23-person161" type="surname" value="Harlow"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17200712-23-person161" type="given" value="Susannah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17200712-23-person161" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             deposed, that she heard the Prisoner say a Week or Fortnight before, that if it was not for the sake of one young Woman, he would set all Wapping on Fire. Two others deposed, that they saw 3 or 4 Persons running along, and that one of them said, there should be a bigger Fire by and by. The Prisoner in his Defence said, that he was afraid of Bailiffs, and had not Money to pay for a Lodging; that he had lain in the Reed-Loft several Nights before; that he smoakt a Pipe of Tobacco that Night before he went up into the Loft, but did not remember that he took the Pipe up with him; that waking and finding the Fire all about his Ears, he ran away from it in a great Fright. He called a great many to his Reputation. The Jury considering the Matter, <rs id="t17200712-23-verdict119" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17200712-23-verdict119" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
